<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1175,1743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,327,1463,1487]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in honor of Michel E. Hendrickx of the Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnología, Unidad Académica Mazatlán, Sinaloa, 
<collectingCountry box="[489,574,1496,1519]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, who has rigorously studied the deep-water benthos of the Golfo de California, and has greatly expanded our understanding of its fauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
