</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1175,1743]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,356,1623,1647]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Comparisons.</emphasis>
Compared to 
<taxonomicName box="[514,778,1624,1647]" class="Bivalvia" family="Periplomatidae" genus="Periploma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anomalodesmata" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="planiusculum">
<emphasis box="[514,778,1624,1647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Periploma planiusculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[794,898,1624,1647]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A – G" captionStartId="2.[151,259,1766,1790]" captionTargetBox="[214,1347,197,1723]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[214,1348,197,1724]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A – G. Periploma skoglundae new species; A – C, E – F, holotype (SBMNH 83429) length = 11 mm. A. Exterior of left valve. B. Interior of left valve. C. Exterior of right valve. D. Dorsal view of both valves joined (paratype SBMNH 149601). E. Hinge of right valve. F. Hinge of left valve. G. Interior of right valve. H – I. Periploma margaritacea (Lamarck, 1801) original illustration from Bruguière (1797: pl. 230, fig. 6 a, b), length = 28 mm. H. Interior of right valve. I. Exterior of right valve. J – O. Periploma kaiserae new species, holotype (SBMNH 149599) length = 15 mm. J. Exterior of left valve. K. Interior of left valve. L. Exterior of right valve. M. Interior of right valve. N. Hinge of right valve. O. Hinge of left valve. P – R. Periploma planiscula Sowerby, 1834, syntype (BMNH 1927.3.4.353) length = 42 mm. P. Exterior of left valve. Q. Interior of left valve. R. Interior of right valve." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276469/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
Figures 
<number box="[885,898,1624,1647]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
P–R), this new species is more equilateral, lacks granules and has low, broad commarginal undulations. It has been reported as 
<taxonomicName authority="Dall, 1896" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1896" box="[1015,1436,1656,1679]" class="Bivalvia" family="Periplomatidae" genus="Periploma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anomalodesmata" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carpenteri" subGenus="Cricoploma">
<emphasis box="[1015,1033,1656,1679]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">P.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1052,1182,1656,1679]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Cricoploma</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1199,1313,1656,1679]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">carpenteri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dall" box="[1320,1436,1656,1679]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" refString="Dall, W. H. (1896) Diagnoses of new species of mollusks from the west coast of America. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 18, 7 - 20." type="journal article" year="1896">
Dall, 
<number box="[1381,1436,1656,1679]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" value="1896.0">1896</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[158,259,1688,1711]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. A – F" captionStartId="3.[151,257,1022,1046]" captionTargetBox="[256,1338,194,1010]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[256,1339,194,1012]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. A – F. Periploma hendrickxi new species, A, C, D, holotype (SBMNH 83628) length = 20 mm, B, E, F, paratype (SBMNH 149600) length = 21 mm. A. Exterior of left valve. B. Interior of left valve. C. Exterior of right valve. D. Dorsal view of both valves joined. E. Hinge of right valve. F. Hinge of right valve. G. Interior of left valve. G – I. Periploma carpenteri Dall, 1896, holotype, USNM 106891 length = 47 mm. G. Interior of right valve. H. Dorsal view of right valve. I. Exterior of left valve." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/276470/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
Figures 
<number box="[246,259,1688,1711]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
G–I), but the latter is circular in shape, has a much larger chondrophore, and weaker commarginal sculpture.
</paragraph>
